accessibility.text: What analysis can I do with Tweetcatcher?
Version 1.3.1 · 2,504 downloads · 31 citations · Last updated 31 Oct 2016 · Licence: GNU-L · Windows PC (XP and above)
Ideal for… clustering, machine learning, data analysis

Tweetcatcher (part of the Chorus suite) allows you to sift Twitter for relevant data in two distinct ways: either by topical keywords appearing in Twitter conversation or by identifying a network of Twitter users and following their daily ‘Twitter lives’.
Navigation · Navigation · Upload your own software

Twitter data can be viewed as a temporally unfolding narrative. Researchers may draw insights from such things as: variation in tweet volume around loci, evolving positive or negative sentiment over the course of a conversation, shifts in the vocabulary characterising a discussion, changes in the likelihood of URLs being referenced within tweets, and so on. In this way, a chronological viewing lends itself to the exploration of ‘events’ as they unfold within Twitter.
Chorus running sentiment analysis on 90,000,000-row data set
